message: Undid revision 592338724 by [[Special:Contributions/Mezigue|Mezigue]] ([[User talk:Mezigue|talk]])what nonsense?  You're the one trying to pretend a particular incarnation does not exist.
Undid revision 592212546 by [[Special:Contributions/DonQuixote|DonQuixote]] ([[User talk:DonQuixote|talk]])Reviewed it.  You're wrong.
Wikipedia also cares about clarity, and not causing meaningless obfuscation through unnecessary and arbitrary distinctions.
Do you actually have a reason for reversing me, or are you reversing for reversing's sake?
Indeed, and the simplest option is having every official and distinct incarnation - as opposed to this arbitrary obsession with series leads, which is confusing and makes little sense at all.

Undid revision 591288380 by [[Special:Contributions/Edokter|Edokter]] ([[User talk:Edokter|talk]]) What gives you the right to dictate that to everyone else?  He was a distinct incarnation, and it makes every sense to include him for that reason.
But none of them are official and distinct incarnations.
Michael Adebolajo and Michael Adebowale admitted killing Rigby - and they were found guilty of murder in court - so there is no reason not to name them in the lead.
/* Views on WW1 centenary */

In that case you will have to leave it for others to agree on, for I see no need to get rid of what seems to me to be highly significant and reasonable sourced material, that is appropriate for a lead.
